  "texts": [
    "Their results align with ours, which further reinforces our conclusions.",
    "Lastly, these insights were also integrated into the instruction-tuning phase of Llama 3 models (Dubey et al., 2024), ensuring that the examples are aligned with pre-training knowledge.",
    "Another line of work explores the model's behavior on new knowledge in test time.",
    "Kang et al. (2024) showed that when a fine-tuned LLM encounters unknown queries at test time, its responses mimic the responses associated with the unknown examples in the fine-tuning data.",
    "Yin et al. (2023) showed that LLMs' performance is not satisfactory when they face new knowledge in their input contexts and Lee et al. (2023) analyzed the impact of unknown in-context learning examples."
